If you erase the most recent snapshot, no problem, just use the one before that. The idea is to keep a running history of versions that you can "roll back" to, <em>not</em> just the previous version.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I guess I'm a little far from writing unit tests as precise as blargg's<br /></div><br />My tests cover proper behavior and make some attempt to find emulator-specific problems, but an emulator author could write much more specific tests that stress the particular design used. For example if the emulator pre-calculates when things will occur, a test could be written to try to confuse the emulator by constantly changing things.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Aug 09, 2006 12:52 pm</p><hr />
