<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1876&amp;p=16065#p16065</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1876&amp;p=16065#p16065"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Something I changed..]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1876&amp;p=16065#p16065"><![CDATA[
Here's a simple way to track down new bugs you introduce: regularly zip up your current source tree and an executable built from it, then when you find a bug, try previous versions until it's gone, then compare the sources and slowly upgrade the working source to the non-working one until the bug re-appears.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Aug 08, 2006 2:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
