<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1876&amp;p=16057#p16057"><![CDATA[
It sounds like there's a flaw in your sprite code code which is somehow causing higher numbered sprites (i.e. ones closer to the end of SPR-RAM) to have higher priority (instead of lower numbered sprites), cover up sprite 0, and cause the hit to not happen (resulting in SMB1 locking up).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Tue Aug 08, 2006 11:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
